-- Zimbabwe's Annual Inflation Rate Fell to 5.3% in June, State Agency Says
-- Brian Latham
-- 2010-07-15T14:12:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/zimbabwe-s-annual-inflation-rate-fell-to-5-3-in-june-state-agency-says.html

          
          
             Zimbabwe’s annual inflation rate
fell to 5.3 percent in June from 6.1 percent a month earlier,
 Moffat Nyoni , director of the government’s statistics office,
said in a phone interview today from the capital, Harare.  
 Prices fell 0.1 percent in June from the previous month,
Nyoni said. Zimbabwe’s statistics office this month changed its
name to Zimstats, he also said.  
